step.reason:
\begin{align}
A &= \int_{0}^{\pi/4}\tan x\, dx = \underbrace{\int_{0}^{\pi/4}
         \dfrac{\sin x}{\cos x}}_{\text{Put }\cos x=t}dx \\
   &=\int_{0}^{\pi/4} -\log \left|\cos x\right|dx \\
   &= \underbrace{-\log\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}}}_{ - \log \,\frac{1}{N} = \log N} + 
         \underbrace{\log 1}_{=0}
     =\log\sqrt{2}= \dfrac{1}{2}\log 2
\end{align}
